<emphasis box="[1272,1276,1747,1770]" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">.</emphasis>
Plant 6-20 cm
<emphasis box="[1449,1453,1747,1770]" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">.</emphasis>
Foliage- leaf solitary, basal, 4-6 x 
<emphasis box="[1131,1140,1775,1798]" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">1</emphasis>
-5-2 cm, elliptical, tapered to a sheath­ ing base which is largely enclosed in a hyaline sheath representing a second basal leaf; a third leaf, small and bract-like, is present on upper part of stem
<emphasis box="[1107,1111,1859,1882]" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">.</emphasis>
Spike short, rather dense; flowers 3-6, greenish-white
<emphasis box="[1015,1019,1887,1910]" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">.</emphasis>
Perianth-segments2-3 mm
<emphasis box="[1323,1327,1887,1910]" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">.</emphasis>
Labellum 3-3-5 mm, rhombic-lanceolate, horizontal or somewhat deflexed
<emphasis box="[1477,1481,1914,1937]" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">.</emphasis>
Spur 2-5-3 mm, curved, half as long as ovary
<emphasis box="[1307,1311,1942,1965]" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">.</emphasis>
2n= 126
<emphasis box="[1419,1423,1942,1965]" pageId="6" pageNumber="331">.</emphasis>
